div.p:
The diuiſion betweene Proteſtant, and Proteſtant; the alienation of affection, betweene Miniſter, and Miniſter; that will neither vouchſafe to ſeeme to conſent, not ioyne together againſt the common aduerſarie, giueth aduant age to the Papiſts. But as the bleſſed Apoſtle ſaith to the Epheſians,
                  Epheſ. 4.4. ſo ſay I, There is but one body, one ſpirit, one hope of our calling, one Lord, one faith, one Baptiſme, one God, and one Father of all. If there be any conſolation in Chriſt, euen for his ſake that made vs, and for his blood that died for vs, let all theſe Ones, make vs one in ye truth;

and while we liue, to keepe the vnity of the ſpirit, in the bond of peace.
